                  :::::::::::::::::FUNCTIONAL STATELESS COMPONENTS::::::::::::::::::
1. State not managed.
2. Easier to Read and Write.
3. Better Performance.
4. No "this" Keyword.
5. Best Practise. 

                  ::::::::::::::::::CLASS COMPONENTS::::::::::::::::::::
1. JavaScript classes introduced in ECMAScript2015 are primarily syntactical 
   sugar over JavaScript's existing prototype based inheritance. 
2. The class syntax is not introducing a new object-oriented inheritance model
   to JavaScript.
3. JavaScript classes provide a much simpler and clearer syntax to create objects
   and deal with inheritance. 
4. What we use in class components?  
   A) "this" Keyword
   B) Lifecycle Methods




